{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3510","heading":"Additional medical and safety standards","label":"3510 Additional medical and safety standards","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/stII/ptB/ch35","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs3510","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe date of enactment of this section, referred to in subsec. (a), is the date of enactment of , which was approved .Pub. L. 117–14May 24, 2021"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Automated External Defibrillators","label":"a .—Automated External Defibrillators","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs3510%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs3510%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"require that the owner of a vessel to which section 3507 applies install, and maintain in working order, automated external defibrillators on such vessel;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs3510%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"require that such defibrillators be placed throughout such vessel in clearly designated locations;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs3510%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"require that such defibrillators are available for passenger and crew access in the event of an emergency; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs3510%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"require that automated external defibrillators, or adjacent equipment, allow passengers and crew to easily contact medical staff of the vessel.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Definition of Owner","label":"b .—Definition of Owner","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s3510","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs3510%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In this section, the term “owner” has the meaning given such term in section 3507.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
